RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman received on Sunday a phone call from French president Emmanuel Macron. The call discussed the situation in Ukraine and the impact of the crisis on energy markets, the Saudi Press Agency reported. The crown prince reiterated Saudi Arabia’s keenness on the stability and balance of oil markets and its commitment to the OPEC+ agreement. The crown prince and Macron also discussed cooperation, the latest regional and international developments, and enhancing international peace and security.